 help keep Alzheimer’s at bay","link":"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/how-the-mind-diet-may-help-keep-alzheimers-at-bay","thumbnail":"https://media.post.rvohealth.io/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2026/03/meal-hands-serving-732x549-thumbnail.jpg","summary":"The MIND diet may help protect the aging brain against structural deterioration, such as grey matter loss, a new study has found."},{"title":"Waist size may be a better predictor of heart failure risk than BMI, study finds","link":"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/waist-size-better-predictor-heart-failure-risk-bmi-study","thumbnail":"https://media.post.rvohealth.io/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2026/03/woman-stretching-woods-732x549-thumbnail.jpg","summary":"A new study indicated that excess fat stored around the waist or visceral fat was more strongly associated with heart failure risk than body mass index (BMI)."},{"title":"Ultra-processed foods may increase heart disease risk, new study finds","link":"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/ultra-processed-foods-may-increase-heart-disease-risk-new-study-finds","thumbnail":"https://media.post.rvohealth.io/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2026/03/Ultra-processed-foods-GettyImages-119453746-Thumb.jpg","summary":"Research in different cohorts confirms that ultra-processed foods are linked to a heightened risk of heart disease. The association is strongest for Black Americans."}],"popularIn":{"title":null,"items":[{"title":"Study introduces 'the Big Bang Theory of migraine'"},{"title":"What you should know about barometric pressure and headaches"},{"title":"What causes a persistent headache?"},{"title":"Can acupressure relieve headaches?"},{"title":"What causes eyebrow pain?"},{"title":"Everything you need to know about migraine"},{"title":"What does a right-sided headache mean?"}]},"countryCode":"TH","forceShowAuth":false,"hidePlacements":[],"userPreloadDrivers":{"headerNewsletter":{"_driverPath":"/articles/headache-chart","_contentIndex":"page","driverId